    <ul class="points">
        <li><b id="fs">File Stream</b>: Transforming files through memory streams instead of hard disk will accelerate the whole transforming task.</li>
        <li><b id="rf">Rest Files</b>: Support picking the rest files, which aren't and will not be selected in the whole task.</li>
        <li><b id="sr">Share Reading</b>: Streams share a file-reading, which avoids duplicated hard disk visiting.</li>
        <li><b id="it">Incremental Transform</b>: File change/remove/add will not affect other files, which makes rerunning very fast.</li>
